SIMPLE: ochreated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ochreated
<hw>O"chre*a`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wearing or
furnished with an ochrea or legging; wearing boots; booted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A scholar undertook . . . to address himself <qex>ochreated</qex>
unto the vice chancellor.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Provided with ochrea, or
sheathformed stipules, as the rhubarb, yellow dock, and
knotgrass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ochreous</ent>⟦br⟧
